Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, put the @Rogan Josh Curry Paste{50%grams} and @Breadcrumbs{10%grams} into
a large #bowl{}, then mix to combine. Add the @Lamb Mince{300%grams}.

Season with the @Salt for the Burgers{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{} then mix together with
your hands.

Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers (1 per
person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a lightly oiled baking tray.

When the fries have ~{15%minutes} left, bake the burgers on the middle shelf of
your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @Lemon{1/2}. Trim the
@Cucumber{1/2}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small
pieces. Cut the @Medium Tomato{1}(chopped) into 1cm chunks.

Squeeze the lemon juice into a large bowl. Mix in the @Sugar for the Dressing{1/2%tsp}
and @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the cucumber and tomato to the dressing and toss together.

Pop the @Burger Buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix together the @Mayonnaise{32%grams} and
@Mango Chutney{40%grams}. Taste and season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if needed.

Once the fries are cooked, sprinkle over the lemon zest and toss to evenly coat.

When everything's ready, spread half the mango chutney mayo over the bun bases.
Top with the lamb burgers and some of the @Wild Rocket{20%grams}, then sandwich
shut with the bun lids.

Serve your craft burgers with the zesty fried alongside.

Toss the remaining rocket with the kachumber salad and serve next to the burgers,
with the rest of the chutney mayo on the side for dipping.

Enjoy!